comments.text: It is a case of the pot calling the kettle black. Hardinghaus and Nenner did exactly the same in their book, ignoring and twisting facts to suit their own narrative. They deliberately chose to ignore the official autopsy report in favor of Jeremy Kryt's articles. The fact that they were banned from Reddit speaks for itself. Hardinghaus and Nenner stalked and threatened people who dared to question them and point out their hypocrisy and double standards. Unfortunately, this is the quality of "journalists"who investigate this sad case. They all have to lie and deceive to create a story.
